  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nUpdating to a new prysm version requires modifying systemd service files, since the executable filename changes.\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nFor easier integration prysm.sh/prysm.bat could create a symlink to the latest version.\r\nExample: \"beacon-chain-linux-amd64\" pointing to \"beacon-chain-v1.0.0-alpha.19-linux-amd64\" \r\n\r\nThis would allow to manually trigger the update using the --download-only option without having to modify other files.\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\nRunning prysm.sh as a service. But that updates on every restart, which is not always wanted and requires write permissions for the executables for the user running beacon or validator.",
